  "notes": [
    "Shaoxing Wu-pinyin to IPA mapping for OCR labels.",
    "Primary spelling inventory follows the Wu Chinese Association Shaoxing romanization page.",
    "Output IPA is constrained to the annotator-provided character inventory: p pʰ b m f v t tʰ d n l s sʰ z ɕ ɕʰ ʑ ȵ k kʰ ɡ ŋ h ɦ ɿ a ᴇ ɤ ɒ o æ̃ ẽ ø̃ ə ø ʔ i u y plus tone digits/superscripts.",
    "Checked-tone finals in the source spelling use q in the hand labels where the published Shaoxing scheme uses h.",
    "2026-05-24 confirmed by annotator: Wu-pinyin final y represents IPA y (iu), not apical ?; legacy ghi-/ghu- spellings are canonicalized to y-/w-; ieq/ieh are canonicalized to iq/ih for checked i?.",
    "2026-05-24 correction: y- is the spelling for ghi- and maps as ?i + final; w- is the spelling for ghu- and maps as ?u + final. Whole yi/yu/wu avoid duplicated high vowels."
  ],
